  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (c0667c5 2022-05-18T00:11:45.21540785Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI am working in a JS monorepo and am getting an error when trying to import contracts from a different package in the monorepo with the error: `File outside of allowed directories`.\r\n\r\nIn JS monorepos, there is a `node_modules` at the base of the directory for shared dependencies between packages and then each package can have a `node_modules` folder for dependencies specific for that package. I'm able to set `nohoist` to keep certain packages in the package's `node_modules` which solves the problem of `forge` not having access to the base `node_modules`, since that will explicitly prevent a dependency from being hoisted to the base, but I still cannot import contracts in other packages in the monorepo. \r\n\r\nThe packages look like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\npackages/\r\n  |- contracts/\r\n  |- contracts-bedrock/\r\n```\r\n\r\n`contracts-bedrock` imports `contracts`, and the JS monorepo set up a symlink in `contracts-bedrock/node_modules` that points to `packages/contract`.\r\n\r\nMy remappings looks like:\r\n```\r\nremappings = [\r\n  '@eth-optimism/contracts/=node_modules/@eth-optimism/contracts/contracts',\r\n  'solmate/=node_modules/@rari-capital/solmate/src',\r\n  'forge-std/=node_modules/forge-std/src',\r\n  'ds-test/=node_modules/ds-test/src'\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy workspace nohoist config looks like:\r\n```\r\n[\r\n  \"@eth-optimism/contracts-bedrock/ds-test\",\r\n  \"@eth-optimism/contracts-bedrock/forge-std\",\r\n  \"@eth-optimism/contracts-bedrock/@rari-capital/solmate\",\r\n  \"@eth-optimism/contracts-bedrock/@eth-optimism/contracts\"\r\n]\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nCould it be possible to either expose the `solc --allow-paths` through `foundry.toml` config or automatically add values if a symlink is detected and add the resolved absolute path of the symlink?",
